theorem nonempty_interior_of_nonempty_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 (A : Set X)) (hNon : (A : Set X).Nonempty) :
    (interior (A : Set X)).Nonempty := by
  classical
  by_contra hInt
  -- From `¬ (interior A).Nonempty`, deduce `interior A = ∅`.
  have hIntEmpty : interior (A : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) :=
    (Set.not_nonempty_iff_eq_empty).1 hInt
  -- Extract a point `x ∈ A` from the non-emptiness of `A`.
  rcases hNon with ⟨x, hxA⟩
  -- `P1` places this point inside `closure (interior A)`.
  have hx_cl : x ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := hP1 hxA
  -- Rewriting with the fact that `interior A = ∅` yields a contradiction.
  have hx_empty : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
    simpa [hIntEmpty, closure_empty] using hx_cl
  cases hx_empty

theorem P2_closure_implies_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (closure (A : Set X)) → Topology.P1 (A : Set X) := by
  intro hP2
  -- From `P2` for `closure A`, deduce that `closure A` is open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (closure (A : Set X)) :=
    Topology.open_of_P2_closure (A := A) hP2
  -- An open closure implies `P1` for the original set.
  exact Topology.closure_open_satisfies_P1 (A := A) hOpen

theorem P2_implies_P3_of_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (A : Set X) → Topology.P3 (interior A) := by
  intro _
  exact Topology.open_satisfies_P3 (A := interior A) isOpen_interior
